  "title": "Absolute-Value Squeeze Theorem",
  "root": "",
  "statement": "Let $(x_n)$ and $(u_n)$ be real sequences, and let $L\\in\\mathbb{R}$.\nSuppose that $u_n\\to 0$. If there exists $N_0\\in\\mathbb{N}$ such that\n$|x_n-L|\\le u_n$ for every $n\\ge N_0$, then $x_n\\to L$.",
